==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|abhomynable}}, from {{der|en|fro|abominable}}, from {{der|en|LL.|abōminābilis||deserving abhorrence}}, from {{m|la|abōminor||abhor, deprecate as an ill omen}}, from {{m|la|ab||from, away from}} + {{m|la|ōminor||forebode, predict, presage}}, from {{m|la|ōmen||sign, token, omen}}. Formerly erroneously [[folk-etymologize]]d as deriving from {{m+|la|ab-}} + {{m|la|homo}} and therefore spelled {{m|en|abhominable}}, {{m|en|abhominal}}; see those entries for more.

